&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hybrid (Morristown, NJ)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT PERFORMLINE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PerformLine is a leading provider of multi-channel marketing compliance technology for enterprises in highly regulated industries. The company&#39;s platform supports pre-publication review of marketing assets and post-publication monitoring across marketing channels including web, social, and email—helping organizations manage risk, ensure regulatory compliance, and protect their brands at scale. PerformLine is headquartered in Morristown, New Jersey, and serves clients across financial services and other regulated markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come as you are. We are an equal opportunity workplace celebrating diversity and committed to creating an inclusive and equitable experience for all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MISSION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is to empower compliance leaders with the technology and knowledge to ensure their organization and partners provide transparent and accurate information to consumers across any channel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR INTERNSHIP PROGRAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our program provides value for our interns both during and after their internship!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PerformLine interns can expect to build valuable skills, knowledge, tools and training through a series of hands-on &quot;prep sessions&quot; to fully prepare them for their next career move. Think mentorship, resume reviews / enhancements, interview training and even mock sessions to practice their new skills!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;**Ask about earning course credit for your university!!**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Data &amp;amp; AI Workflows&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use Claude and other AI tools to extract, clean, and transform large client data sets — building repeatable, AI-assisted workflows instead of one-off manual pulls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze data and surface actionable insights, using Claude to accelerate exploration, summarization, and reporting within the product interface&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain tracking of client-specific reporting goals based on quotas and capacity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct industry research (federal regulation, speech analytics, internet protocols) and use AI to synthesize findings and apply them to team processes in real time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build comprehensive playbooks and prompt guides to add to our training library&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;AI &amp;amp; Automation Support / QA&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test AI and automation tools by running structured test cases, evaluating outputs, and flagging failures or edge cases for engineering follow-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify candidates for AI automation by spotting repetitive manual tasks based on volume, repeatability, and error rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle exceptions and edge cases that AI can&#39;t yet manage, applying judgment where human review is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use SQL and AI-assisted checks to validate that automated and AI-generated outputs match expected results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track QA outcomes across AI/automation rollouts, noting regressions and gaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reports that measure AI/automation impact vs. manual baseline (time saved, error reduction, task deflection)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
